description:
&lt;p&gt;MAU Bedwas Ward at Ysbyty Ystrad Fawr (YYF) are looking for an enthusiastic Registered Nurse to join our friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bedwas Ward consists of 28 en suite rooms. We specialise in Acute Medicine, and also have a 14 bed Emergency Frailty Unit, supported by an EFU team. The medical assessment Unit is a 9 bed assessment unit which takes medical referrals from MIU and GP’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is open to all registered nurses and we offer a supportive induction programme to ensure staff are given the skills to work in all areas, which will include shifts throughout the 24 hour period. We foster a continuous learning working environment including simulation scenarios on the ward, and have a ANP&#39;s and Medics in the area who are keen to provide teaching and support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for innovative and enthusiastic individuals who will adopt a patient centered approach to care, and in return offer the opportunity to work with a skilled team who are keen to develop staff and their clinical skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 22nd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Grandon&lt;br /&gt;Tel: 01443 802226&lt;/p&gt;
